{
  "title": "Planet Hunting 2",
  "publicationStatus": "public",
  "labEnvironment": "production",
  "subtitle": "Seeing Star Motion With a Telescope: The Effect of Tilt",
  "category": "",
  "subCategory": "",
  "screenshot": "",
  "aspectRatio": 1.8,
  "fontScale": 0.7,
  "lang": "en-US",
  "i18nMetadata": "",
  "helpOnLoad": false,
  "aboutOnLoad": true,
  "about": [
    "Explore which planetary angles of orbit can be detected by scientists on Earth.",
    "",
    "In this model, the telescope is at a right angle (90Â°) to the screen. ",
    "(Imagine that you are looking through a telescope focused on the screen to see the star's motion ",
    "toward and away from you.).",
    "Not all star motion will be detected by this telescope.",
    "",
    "Change the tilt of the orbit by dragging the gridded plane of the model. The current tilt angle is reported in ",
    "the lower left of the model.",
    "",
    "Which orbital angles can the telescope detect?",
    "",
    "(Note that you may need to **Zoom** in on the graph after changing the planet's orbital angle (tilt). You can also clear ",
    "current graph data to focus on the newer data only.)"
  ],
 "credits": ["This [High-Adventure Science](http://has.concord.org \"High-Adventure Science\") interactive ",
              "was developed under a series of grants from the [National Science Foundation](http://nsf.gov \"National Science Foundation\") ",
              "(DRL-0929774, DRL-1220756 ) in partnership with the ",
              "[National Geographic Society](http://nationalgeographic.org/education/ \"National Geographic Society\")."],
  "theme": [
    "has",
    "standalone-playback",
    "no-slider-bar",
    "graph-title-bg"
  ],
  "showTopBar": true,
  "showBottomBar": true,
  "padding": 10,
  "models": [
    {
      "type": "iframe-model",
      "id": "iframe-model",
      "url": "models/lab-version/1/iframe-model/iframe-model.json",
      "onLoad": [],
      "viewOptions": {
        "controlButtons": "play_reset"
      },
      "modelOptions": {
        "url": "//concord-consortium.github.io/space-models/planet-hunting/",
        "timestep": 0.001,
        "planet.diameter": 10,
        "planet.rocky": true,
        "telescope.precision": 100
      }
    }
  ],
  "propertiesToRetain": [],
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "speed",
      "initialValue": 50,
      "onChange": [
        "var v = value / 50;",
        "if (v > 1) v = Math.pow(v, 4);",
        "if (v < 1) v = Math.sqrt(v);",
        "set('timestep', 0.001 * v);"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "outputs": [
    {
      "name": "time",
      "value": "return iframeOutput('time') * 365 || 0;"
    },
    {
      "name": "starCamVelocity",
      "value": "return iframeOutput('telescope.starCamVelocity') || 0;"
    },
    {
      "name": "camera.tilt",
      "value": "return iframeOutput('camera.tilt') || 0;"
    }
  ],
  "filteredOutputs": [],
  "helpTips": [],
  "dataSets": [],
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "clear-graphs",
      "type": "button",
      "action": [
        "var newXMin = Math.round(get('time'));",
        "var newXMax = newXMin + 600;",
        "setComponentAttributes('star-cam-velocity', {xmin: newXMin, xmax: newXMax});"
        ],
      "text": "Clear graph",
      "width": "",
      "height": "",
      "disabled": false,
      "tooltip": "",
      "helpIcon": false
    },
    {
      "id": "timestep",
      "type": "slider",
      "min": 1,
      "max": 100,
      "steps": 100,
      "title": "Speed",
      "titlePosition": "top",
      "fillColor": "#2DA343",
      "labels": [
        {
          "value": 1,
          "label": "slow"
        },
        {
          "value": 100,
          "label": "fast"
        }
      ],
      "width": "auto",
      "height": "auto",
      "property": "speed",
      "retainProperty": true,
      "disabled": false,
      "tooltip": "",
      "helpIcon": false
    },
    {
      "id": "star-cam-velocity",
      "type": "graph",
      "resetAxesOnReset": true,
      "enableAutoScaleButton": true,
      "enableAxisScaling": false,
      "enableZooming": false,
      "autoScaleX": true,
      "autoScaleY": true,
      "enableSelectionButton": false,
      "clearSelectionOnLeavingSelectMode": false,
      "enableDrawButton": false,
      "drawProperty": null,
      "markAllDataPoints": false,
      "showRulersOnSelection": false,
      "fontScaleRelativeToParent": true,
      "hideAxisValues": false,
      "properties": [
        "starCamVelocity"
      ],
      "xProperty": "time",
      "title": "Velocity of Star, Relative to Observer",
      "titlePosition": "left",
      "buttonsStyle": "text",
      "buttonsLayout": "horizontal",
      "lineWidth": 2,
      "width": "100%",
      "height": "100%",
      "xlabel": "Time (days)",
      "xmin": 0,
      "xmax": 600,
      "ylabel": "Velocity (m/s)",
      "ymin": -0.2,
      "ymax": 0.2,
      "xTickCount": 8,
      "yTickCount": 4,
      "xscaleExponent": 0.5,
      "yscaleExponent": 0.5,
      "xFormatter": ".2r",
      "yFormatter": ".2s",
      "lines": true,
      "bars": false,
      "tooltip": "",
      "dataColors": [
        "#0000ff"
      ],
      "legendLabels": [],
      "legendVisible": false,
      "syncYAxis": false,
      "helpIcon": false
    },
    {
      "id": "playback",
      "type": "playback",
      "stepping": true
    }
  ],
  "layout": {
    "playback-container": [
      "playback"
    ],
    "playback-right": [
      "timestep"
    ],
    "right-top": [
      "star-cam-velocity"
    ],
    "under-graphs": [
      "clear-graphs"
    ]
  },
  "template": [
    {
      "id": "playback-container",
      "top": "model.bottom",
      "left": "model.left",
      "padding-top": "0.75em",
      "padding-right": "0.5em"
    },
    {
      "id": "playback-right",
      "top": "model.bottom",
      "left": "playback-container.right"
    },
    {
      "id": "right-top",
      "left": "model.right",
      "height": "model.height",
      "width": "20em",
      "padding-left": "0.3em",
      "padding-right": "0.3em"
    },
    {
      "id": "under-graphs",
      "left": "right-top.left",
      "right": "right-top.right",
      "top": "right-top.bottom",
      "align": "right",
      "margin-right": "1em",
      "margin-top": "1em"
    }
  ]
}
